		RULES BEFORE YOU OPT FOR A RACE

1. The window will show the text to be typed as it is(case sensitive).
2. Every incorrect character typed will display highlighted '^'. 
   you can correct the character using 'BACKSPACE'.  
3. When a character is typed incorrectly, you can change it unlimited 
   number of times. Remember, it affects your accuracy.
4. Do not add a newline character after you have completed typing the
   entire text displayed.
5. Two typing speeds(net & gross) will be displayed at the right corner 
   of the screen once you are done typing the entire text.
6. If you are done reading the above points then START THE RACE!!
